Two Russian Ka-52 attack helicopters were shot down by the Ukrainian military over the Skadovsk district, Kherson region, in the south of Ukraine bordering the temporarily occupied Crimea. One of the pilots survived the crash and was taken to a hospital. A video showing one of the downed copters was also released. It shows that the aircraft’s registration No. RF-13409. UN Chief Seeks End To Syria War France To Offer Fuel Rebate To Help Motorists As Ukrinform reported earlier, referring to the Army’s General Staff, as of March 12, Russian invaders’ death toll stood at over 12,000, while hardware losses included 362 tanks, 58 aircraft, 135 artillery systems, 83 helicopters, and more.This was reported by the Land Forces Command, Ukrinform reports.